==English==
===Etymology===
From the Latin ''versus'': against, past participle of ''vertere'': turn, turn around; change, alter; overthrow, destroy

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)səs|-ɜː(r)səs]]

===Preposition===
'''versus'''

# against, in opposition to.
:''It is the Patriots '''versus''' the Eagles in the 2005 Superbowl.''

====Translations====

* French : [[contre]]
* Icelandic: [[á móti]]
* [[Ido]] : [[kontre]]
* Swedish : [[mot]], [[kontra]] (''rare'')


